## API Layer

### REST (`src/api/client.ts`)

Used only for the `/setup/*` routes (Auth0 JWT bearer token).

- `GET /setup/me` — current user profile
- `GET /setup/tenants` — list user's tenants
- `POST /setup/tenants` — create tenant + first API key

### Socket.IO (`src/api/socket.ts`)

The socket layer manages connections to all backend namespaces. Each namespace
has a dedicated `connect*`, `disconnect*`, and `emit*` helper exported from
`socket.ts`.

#### `connectAll(token)` — connects all domain namespaces at once

| Namespace    | Store(s)                   | Key events (server → client)              |
| ------------ | -------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `/tenants`   | `tenant`                   | Session, tenant list                      |
| `/endpoints` | `endpoints`, `status`      | `connection_status`, endpoint CRUD        |
| `/tools`     | `tools`                    | `tools_changed`, tool queries             |
| `/keys`      | `tenant`                   | API key CRUD                              |
| `/users`     | `users`                    | User list, role updates (admin only)      |
| `/i18n`      | _(global)_                 | Error code + key translation (public)     |

> **Removed:** The `/chat` namespace was removed. LLM generation and AI key
> management are now handled via HTTP (`POST /api/chat` and `/api/ai-keys`).

#### Socket readiness gate

`socket.ts` exports `markSocketReady()` / `resetSocketReady()`. All `emit()`
calls are queued until `markSocketReady()` is called from `App.vue` after full
initialisation. This prevents race conditions on page reload.

> **Note:** The `/chat` namespace no longer exists. LLM generation was migrated
> to stateless HTTP SSE (`POST /api/chat`). Socket.IO is still used for all
> other real-time features (endpoints, tools, keys, tenants, users).

### MCP Streamable HTTP (`src/api/mcpClient.ts`)

A thin client used exclusively by the **Ollama** chat path to call MCP tools.

- Maintains one `sessionId` per tenant API key.
- On 404 (server restart), transparently re-initialises the session and retries once.
- Methods: `initialize(key)`, `callTool(name, args, key)`, `deleteSession()`.

### HTTP SSE Transport (`src/api/chatTransport.ts`)

Streamline transport for **all non-Ollama providers** (OpenAI, Anthropic,
Gemini, GitHub Models). Posts to the backend `POST /api/chat` and parses
the Vercel AI SDK UIMessageStream SSE response.

- Uses `parseJsonEventStream()` + `uiMessageChunkSchema` from the `ai` npm
  package (client-side only for SSE parsing).
- Converts `ChatMessage[]` → `UIMessage[]` (parts-based wire format).
- Maps SSE chunk types to callbacks:
  - `text-delta` → `onToken` (cumulative text)
  - `reasoning-delta` → thinking in `onToken`
  - `tool-input-available` / `tool-output-available` / `tool-output-error` → `onToolCall`
  - `finish` → `onDone` with token usage
  - `error` / `abort` → `onError`

---

## Chat System

The chat system was migrated from a **Socket.IO `/chat` namespace** to a
**stateless HTTP SSE architecture** powered by **Vercel AI SDK** (`ai` npm
package) on both the backend and frontend.

### Chat Modes

The user selects a mode via `ChatModeSelector` in the input area. The mode
is persisted in `chatSettings.chatMode`.

| Mode      | Description                                                                                    |
| --------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Ask**   | Single-turn generation. The LLM responds with text and may call tools (agentic loop on backend).|
| **Plan**  | The LLM generates a structured plan (title + tasks). The user can edit, approve, or reject.     |
| **Agent** | An approved plan is executed: each task is run as an isolated LLM generation with tool access.  |

### Generation orchestration (`useChatGeneration.ts`)

`useChatGeneration` is the main entry point called by `ChatView.vue`. It
routes to the appropriate execution path based on mode:

- **Ask** → `useChat().generate()` directly.
- **Plan** → `usePlanning().createPlan()` streams a markdown plan, parsed
  into an `AgentPlan` with `parseMarkdownPlan()`.
- **Agent** → `useAgentOrchestrator().runAgentMode()` waits for plan
  approval via the `agentPlanning` store, then executes.

### Provider dispatch (`src/composables/useChat.ts`)

`useChat` dispatches based on `chatSettings.settings.provider`:

| Provider      | Execution path                     | Tool call path                        |
| ------------- | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `"ollama"`    | `useOllama` (direct browser fetch) | `mcpClient.ts` → backend `/mcp`      |
| `"openai"`    | HTTP SSE → `ChatController`        | `McpProxyManager` (server-side)       |
| `"anthropic"` | HTTP SSE → `ChatController`        | `McpProxyManager` (server-side)       |
| `"gemini"`    | HTTP SSE → `ChatController`        | `McpProxyManager` (server-side)       |
| `"github"`    | HTTP SSE → `ChatController`        | `McpProxyManager` (server-side)       |

For non-Ollama providers, the backend's `ChatController` uses Vercel AI SDK's
`streamText()` with `stepCountIs(maxIterations)` for agentic tool-call loops.
SSE is streamed via `pipeUIMessageStreamToResponse()` through Fastify's
`reply.hijack()`.

### Plan generation (`usePlanning.ts`)

Streams a structured markdown prompt to the LLM. The response is parsed into
an `AgentPlan { title, parallelGroups: AgentTask[][] }`. The user can edit
tasks (add, remove, reorder, rename) before approving. First-person
noun-phrase planning prompt for natural task decomposition.

### Agent execution (`useAgentOrchestrator.ts`)

After approval, parallel groups execute with `Promise.all`, sequential groups
run in order. Each task gets an isolated `useChat()` instance. It respects
the session system prompt override: `task.systemPrompt ?? sessionSystemPrompt
?? settings.systemPrompt`.

### Context window summarization (`useContextSummarizer.ts`)

When token usage reaches ≥85% of the context window, older messages are
compressed into a summary. The last 4 user/assistant pairs are kept verbatim.
Falls back to character-based estimation when token count is unavailable.

### System prompt composition

In **Ask** mode, only the base system prompt is used. In **Plan** and **Agent**
modes, the base system prompt is concatenated with `PLANNING_SYSTEM_PROMPT`.
A per-session prompt override can be set via `ChatSessionPromptBar`.

### Tool Manager

The tool count badge in `ChatInput` footer opens `ToolManagerModal`. Tools
are grouped by endpoint with master + individual toggles. Disabled tools
are persisted in `localStorage` (`mcp-central:disabled-tools`) and excluded
from all LLM generation calls via `toolStore.activeTools`.

### Chat sessions

Sessions (messages, title, tenantId, systemPrompt?) are persisted in
`localStorage` via the `chat` store. No session data is stored on the backend.

### LLM provider key management

OpenAI / Anthropic / Gemini / GitHub keys are stored **encrypted on the
backend** via `AiKeysController` HTTP routes (`GET/POST/DELETE /api/ai-keys`).
The frontend only ever sees the `keyHint` (last 4 chars). Keys are never
stored in `localStorage`.

MCP session keys are auto-provisioned per tenant via
`GET /api/ai-keys/mcp-session` (composable `useChatMcpSession.ts`).

---

## Authentication Flow

1. User visits `/` → `LandingView` shows Auth0 login button.
2. Auth0 redirect/popup → `auth0-vue` stores the access token **in memory**.
3. `App.vue` calls `authStore.init()` → fetches user profile from `GET /setup/me`.
4. `App.vue` calls `tenantStore.init()` → fetches tenants from `GET /setup/tenants`.
5. `App.vue` calls `connectAll(token)` → opens all Socket.IO namespaces.
6. `App.vue` emits `selectTenant` on `/tenants` with the active `tenantId`.
7. `markSocketReady()` unblocks all queued `emit()` calls.

On logout: `disconnectAll()` closes all sockets, stores are reset.

On socket reconnection: the frontend re-emits `selectTenant` to restore the
active tenant room across all namespaces.

---

## Settings View

`SettingsView.vue` is a single route (`/settings`) with a tabbed left-nav.
Tabs are rendered dynamically — **Users** tab is only visible to admins.

| Tab id    | Component           | Content                                      |
| --------- | ------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| `profile` | `SettingsProfile`   | Auth0 name, email, role display              |
| `tenants` | `SettingsTenants`   | Create / delete tenants (admins see all)     |
| `keys`    | `SettingsKeys`      | Create / revoke API keys for active tenant   |
| `ai`      | `SettingsAI`        | Provider selector, model, LLM key storage, Ollama URL |
| `a2a`     | `SettingsA2A`       | Copyable A2A v1.0 endpoint URLs (public card, extended card, message endpoints) |
| `users`   | `SettingsUsers`     | Admin — list all users, promote/demote roles |

---

## i18n

All user-facing strings are in `src/locales/en.ts`. Components never contain
hardcoded user-facing text.

The `/i18n` Socket.IO namespace (backend) provides runtime translation of error
codes returned by the API and Socket.IO callbacks. The frontend falls back to
the `message` field if the translation is unavailable.

---

## Error Handling Convention

- HTTP / Socket.IO errors always carry a `code` field (e.g. `ERR_AUTH_KEY_INVALID`).
- `useError.ts` normalises errors into a `{ code, message }` shape.
- **Contextual errors** (400, 404, 409): displayed inline, next to the relevant field or list.
- **Global errors** (500, network, auth 401): toasted via the `toast` store.
- Never silently swallow errors. Every error must surface to the user.

---

## Development Rules

1. **Vue 3 Composition API only.** `<script setup>` in all components.
2. **TypeScript strict.** No `any` unless documented.
3. **Tailwind utility classes only.** No custom CSS except for design tokens in CSS variables.
4. **Pinia stores for shared state.** Composables for reusable logic.
5. **Tokens in memory only.** The Auth0 access token lives in `authStore` (memory), never in `localStorage`.
6. **API keys are secrets.** Shown once on creation via a modal with copy button. Never logged.
7. **i18n from day one.** No hardcoded user-facing strings — always use `t()`.
8. **Empty states everywhere.** Every list view has a meaningful `EmptyState` with a CTA.
9. **Loading states everywhere.** Skeleton loaders for initial fetches, spinners for actions.
10. **Session recovery.** After any socket reconnect, re-emit `selectTenant` to restore the tenant room.
